      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, even small obstructions, such as insects, can have a significant impact on a pitot tube's functionality. They can cause turbulence and create additional resistance to the airflow, leading to inaccurate airspeed readings. Regular maintenance and thorough visual inspections can help catch and resolve these issues before they pose a serious risk to the aircraft's operation. While the likelihood and consequences may be smaller than larger obstructions, we count even these minor factors when evaluating pitot tube integrity.",
